In order to protect infants and children from serious '''[[infectious disease]]s''', the [[Department of Health]] of [[Hong Kong]] provides a free comprehensive childhood [[vaccination|immunisation programme]] to [[Hongkongers]] over all the Maternal & Child Health Centres. For primary 1 and primary 6 students, Department of Health dispatches immunisation teams to schools for the required vaccinations.
